{"lemma":"دالِيَةٍ","slug":"دالِيَةٍ","root":"د.ل.#","root_slug":"د-ل-_","root_link":"/words/roots/د-ل-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13021"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"noria, waterwheel"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"vine"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"espalier, railing"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"deltoid"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"varix; varicosis"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From دَلْو (dalw, “bucket”) or related دَلَا (dalā, “to suspend, to let down in the water”) in the sense of a waterwheel; in all other senses presumed semantic loan from Aramaic דָלִיתָא / ܕܳܠܻܝܬ݂ܳܐ (dālīṯā, “vine; varicose vein”), although the sense of the deltoid muscle appears to be an Arabic figurative development from the idea of an espalier, which disregarded the more traditional medical sense."},"ipa":["/daː.li.ja/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13021","headword_ar":"دَالِيَةٌ","root":"dlw","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water-wheel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"machine for irrigating land, such as is called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manojanuwn","text_ar":"مَنْجَنُون"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is turned by an ox or a cow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAEuwrap","text_ar":"نَاعُورَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nAEwrp","text_ar":"ناعورة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is turned by water: (S:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing made of palm-leaves"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and pieces of wood, with which water is drawn"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for irrigating land"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by means of ropes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cords,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) [app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"held and drawn at one end by a man, and at the other end"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tied to a tall palm-trunk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bucket"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dalow","text_ar":"دَلْو"},{"kind":"text","text":"), and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, with pieces of wood made in the form of a cross,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with two pieces of wood placed across and so tied together,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two arms of which are bound to the top"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rim"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the bucket; them one end of a rope is tied to it, and the other end to a palm-trunk standing at the head of the well; and one irrigates"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with it"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by drawing and swinging it up by means of another, or of the same, rope"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: the word is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEilapN","text_ar":"فَاعِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlapN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[because it is pulled up]: the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dawaAlK","text_ar":"دَوَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": El-Fárábee deviates from others, by explaining it as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manojanuwn","text_ar":"مَنْجَنُون"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and J follows him: (Msb:) [a similar apparatus for irrigating land is used in the northern parts of Egypt, called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTowap","text_ar":"قَطْوَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dalow","text_ar":"دَلْو","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": it consists of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bowl-shaped bucket, with four cords attached to its rim: two men, each holding two of the cords, throw up the water by means of it into a trough or trench:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to Mtr,] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAliyap","text_ar":"دَالِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tall palm-trunk set in the manner of the machine with which rice is beaten"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to remove the husks"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having at its head a large bowl, with which water is drawn"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for irrigating land"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Land that is irrigated by means of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dalow","text_ar":"دَلْو"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bucket"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"machine called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manojanuwn","text_ar":"مَنْجَنُون"},{"kind":"text","text":"[mentioned above]. (M, K.) ―         -b3-  And the pl.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dawaAlK","text_ar":"دَوَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Unripe dates hung, and eaten when they become ripe."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hung fruit."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in liii. 8. [But perhaps"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alvmr","text_ar":"الثمر"},{"kind":"text","text":"is there a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~moru","text_ar":"التّمْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b4-  Also (i. e. the pl.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Black grapes, but not intensely black,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the bunches of which are the largest of all bunches, appearing like goats hung"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the vines"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the berries thereof are coarse, breaking in the mouth, and round; and are dried."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, M.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dawaAliY~u","text_ar":"دَوَالِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dwAl","text_ar":"دوال"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b5-  [The sing. also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A grape-vine"},{"kind":"text","text":"itself: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a shoot"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a grape-vine: pl. as above.]"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","Msb","AHn"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}